BENIN – The Delta State Command of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) has given owners of two trucks abandoned at the command’s premises at Asaba which interim forfeiture has been ordered by the Federal High Court sitting in Warri to come forward within 15 days to face prosecution, failure which, the trucks will be forfeited to the Federal government. A statement issued by the command’s spokesman, Emeka Peters (DSC) stated that the Delta State Command of NSCDC wish to notify owners of two trucks with registration number, SUL 484 XA and NNR 152 XA respectively, abandoned at the premises of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps, Delta State Command, Asaba, to make themselves available within 15 days for prosecution or have the trucks forfeited. According to the statement, “the general public is hereby notified that failure of the owner(s) of the aforementioned trucks to submit themselves for prosecution within 15 days, the said Order which was made on the 13th of May 2022 at the Federal High Court sitting in Warri Delta State shall become absolute”